of probability, pH is probability in H, 1 ‚àí Œ± is the level of conÔ¨Ådence and A is the accuracy. This
probability is held in the interval [0.045 0.055]. The number of runs has to be runs ‚â• T . Only
1 ‚àí Œ± values over 0.90 are reliable. In our case we chose 0.95. As the aim of this work is to get
a tool for good accurate results the A of 0.0002. Due to the interval that we are working with
our pH is 0.05. Replacing these values in the previous formula we solve and get the number of
runs.
